messages.message:
hi team - i am facing the below error on aihub.instabase.com (http://aihub.instabase.com) for any file that i am trying to upload.

Can someone please help me with this?
same thing happens on aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com (http://aihub-uat.internal.instabase.com)
Here is the trace_id for the request: `ca8e9fe6fa0c23ac`

Looks like there is an error in File service:

`grpc_message:"Failure during stat - file not found. Path: aihub/6249bf40-4085-45f7-b2ee-685edca90117/project/reader_profiles/default.ibreader"}"`
i can do a quick screenshare if the issue persists. aihib prod is working fine for me
cc <!subteam^S05BKH20B4K> if needed
<!subteam^S05TRT53J8N>
this doesn't look to be the reader issue; the UI is build, this just shows that the default reader profile for a project is missing
@Piyush, did you configure any of these Project settings differently than their default values for this project?
did you see a project migration window for this project?
@Arjun do you know if we copy the ibreader file for project migration?
I’m not sure the details of how projects get migrated cc @daniel. I did just try on a migrated project on prod and it failed

looks to be a separate issue though:
```"Merging staging directory failed. Failures: [AddFileFailure(reason='While listing staging directory: Folder aihub/47f53b34-b3cd-4e4e-8762-95622767d192/documents/staging/4f02b42a-2653-4433-9afa-08ac37360e6b does not exist: <nil>', stage=<FailureStage.STAGING: 0>, staging_file_path='erich/my-repo/fs/Instabase Drive/aihub/47f53b34-b3cd-4e4e-8762-95622767d192/documents/staging/4f02b42a-2653-4433-9afa-08ac37360e6b', raw_file_path=None, processed_file_path=None, input_file_id=None, project_doc_id=None)]"```

that error comes after this
```"An unexpected error has occured: Field missing. 'profiles'"```
so might be related
@andy i didnt change anything. I can screen share if thats helpful
I think @Eric Han and team is on this; Eric, please reach out to Piyush offline to get this sorted
this does seem to be related to project migration — @Piyush I would recommend creating a new project for the time being to unblock
We don’t create a default reader profile upon migration, which seems to be the issue here.
Thank you - creating a new project worked
the `profiles` error indicates that the reader profile is malformed. It must contain the `profiles: List` key.
